"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:3.1.3\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">3.1.3</span> Gate or gateway to house or building complex</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">References:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">אַיִל</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(’ayil)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs6:31\">1KI 6:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:9\">EZK 40:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:9\">EZK 40:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:10\">EZK 40:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:14\">EZK 40:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:14\">EZK 40:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:16\">EZK 40:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:16\">EZK 40:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:21\">EZK 40:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:21\">EZK 40:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:24\">EZK 40:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:24\">EZK 40:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:26\">EZK 40:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:26\">EZK 40:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:29\">EZK 40:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:29\">EZK 40:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:31\">EZK 40:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:31\">EZK 40:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:33\">EZK 40:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:34\">EZK 40:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:34\">EZK 40:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:36\">EZK 40:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:36\">EZK 40:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:37\">EZK 40:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:37\">EZK 40:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:37\">EZK 40:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:37\">EZK 40:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:38\">EZK 40:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:48\">EZK 40:48</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:49\">EZK 40:49</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek41:1\">EZK 41:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek41:3\">EZK 41:3</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">פֶּתַח</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(pethach)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam11:9\">2SA 11:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs14:27\">1KI 14:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr12:10\">2CH 12:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer43:9\">JER 43:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek8:7\">EZK 8:7</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">פֶּתֶח, שַׁעַר</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(pethach sha‘ar)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg18:16\">JDG 18:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg18:17\">JDG 18:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer36:10\">JER 36:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek8:3\">EZK 8:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek8:14\">EZK 8:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek10:19\">EZK 10:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek11:1\">EZK 11:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:11\">EZK 40:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:40\">EZK 40:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek46:3\">EZK 46:3</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">שַׁעַר</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(sha‘ar)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth2:19\">EST 2:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth2:21\">EST 2:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth3:2\">EST 3:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth3:3\">EST 3:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth4:2\">EST 4:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth4:2\">EST 4:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth4:6\">EST 4:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth5:9\">EST 5:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth5:13\">EST 5:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth6:10\">EST 6:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth6:12\">EST 6:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:3\">EZK 40:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:6\">EZK 40:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:6\">EZK 40:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:8\">EZK 40:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:11\">EZK 40:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:11\">EZK 40:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:14\">EZK 40:14</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">שַׁעַר, אִיתוֹן</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(sha‘ar ’iton)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:15\">EZK 40:15</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">προαύλιον</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(proaulion)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:68\">MRK 14:68</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">πυλών</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(pulōn)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:71\">MAT 26:71</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:20\">LUK 16:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:17\">ACT 10:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:13\">ACT 12:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:14\">ACT 12:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:14\">ACT 12:14</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Description:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>The gateway was the area associated with the entrance into the courtyard of a house or other building.</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Translation:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:0\">EZK 40:0</a> –<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek41:0\">EZK 41:0</a>: These chapters contain a detailed and complicated description of a large entrance complex leading into the Temple of Ezekiel’s vision. This complex was made up of nine or ten different rooms or areas, some of them described with more than one term. The narrative description of the entrance complex and of the entire Temple is very difficult to understand without reference to diagrams of some sort. Translators should consider using diagrams of Ezekiel’s Temple similar to those provided in this Handbook (see <a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">3.14.1 Jewish Temple&lt;REALIA:3.14.1&gt;</a>).</p>\n<p>The meaning of the Hebrew word <em>’ayil</em> in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:0\">EZK 40:0</a> –<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek41:0\">EZK 41:0</a> is disputed. Some translations understand it to be a pillar that stands flush with the wall or with the sides of an entranceway; for example, <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> renders it “jambs” (see <a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">3.1.2.4 Doorpost&lt;REALIA:3.1.2.4&gt;</a>). In this case it would form only part of the entrance but could be understood to stand for the whole entrance.</p>\n<p>\n            <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> has rendered the Greek word <em>pulōn</em> as “porch” in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:71\">MAT 26:71</a>. For speakers of American English, this is misleading. <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> “entrance of the courtyard” is better. Other possibilities are “entryway” and “passageway.”</p>\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:13\">ACT 12:13</a>: Here Peter knocks on “the door of the <em>pulōn</em> ” and waits outside until it is opened. This was either the door leading from the street into the inner court or else a smaller door built into the main door of the gate, which could be used for entrance without opening the larger main one. <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New American Standard Bible\">NASB</abbr> “the door of the gate” is accurate but less than clear. Most translations render it “the outer door” or “the outside door.” Some languages may have a single word for this special door; for example, <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"German Common Language Version (Gute Nachricht Bibel)\">GECL</abbr> uses a single German word meaning “courtyard-gate”). <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Spanish Common Language Version (Dios Habla Hoy)\">SPCL</abbr> “street entrance” may also serve as a model.</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
